<p>The ETF provider chooses the index, manages replication, handles tax and legal structure, lends securities if permitted, and keeps the fund operating smoothly across exchanges. In Europe, providers also decide whether to offer <strong>accumulating</strong> or <strong>distributing</strong> share classes, hedge currency risk, and list the same ETF in multiple trading currencies and markets.</p>
